title: The Carnival of Venice
provenance: Given by Mrs. James Ward Throne
medium: Brush and watercolor, Engraving in black ink on paper
description: Scene with dancing figures.  Palace of the Doges on right, library on left.  Also the campanile of St. Marks, the Mint, and a church.  Right edge of each section taped to folding cardboard mount of which parts G and H are cross members.
